---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import CTABanner from '../../components/CTABanner.astro';
import { SUITES } from '../../lib/constants';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Agent Suites — 1404 | AI Agent Teams for Business Operations"
  description="Five specialized agent suites that handle executive operations, financial intelligence, business development, acquisitions, and exit preparation. Purpose-built for your business."
>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-40 pb-24 md:pb-32">
    <SectionHeading
      title="Agent Suites"
      subtitle="Each suite is a team of specialized AI agents built for a specific operational function in your company."
    />

    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        An agent suite is a team of AI agents trained on your business and connected to your actual systems — not a chatbot or a tool with a login, but a group of specialized workers that handle an entire operational function the way a department would, except they run around the clock and get better the longer they operate.
      </p>
      <p>
        You pick the function that's costing you the most time or money. We build the agent team, connect it to your email, your financials, your CRM, whatever systems that function touches. Then we manage it on an ongoing basis — tuning, expanding, fixing things when they break. You don't need to understand how any of it works — you just stop doing that work yourself.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most companies start with one suite and add more once they see what it actually looks like to have a function running without someone doing it manually. There's no commitment to buy all five — just start with the one that would save you the most time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Suite Cards -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <SectionHeading title="The five suites" />

      <div class="space-y-10">
        {SUITES.map((suite) => (
          <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-8 bg-bg-card">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between gap-4 mb-4">
              <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-text-primary">
                <a href={`/agents/${suite.slug}`} class="hover:text-copper transition-colors duration-200">
                  {suite.name}
                </a>
              </h3>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-muted font-mono shrink-0">
                Replaces: {suite.replaces}
              </p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
              {suite.description}
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-2 mb-6">
              {suite.skills.slice(0, 5).map((skill) => (
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm flex items-start gap-2">
                  <span class="text-copper mt-0.5 shrink-0">&bull;</span>
                  {skill}
                </p>
              ))}
            </div>
            <a href={`/agents/${suite.slug}`} class="text-sm text-copper hover:text-copper-bright transition-colors duration-200">
              Learn more &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What's Included -->
  <section class="border-t border-border">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32">
      <SectionHeading title="What every suite includes" />

      <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mb-12">
        Every suite ships with the same foundation. The agents are different, the skills are different, but the infrastructure and the level of service are the same regardless of which function you're automating.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-6 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-3 tracking-wide">TRAINED ON YOUR BUSINESS</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Agents learn your terminology, your preferences, your workflows, and your standards. They're not generic — they're built specifically for how your company operates.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-6 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-3 tracking-wide">CONNECTED TO YOUR SYSTEMS</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Email, CRM, accounting, project management, file storage — whatever systems the function touches, the agents are wired into them directly. No manual data entry, no copy-paste.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-6 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-3 tracking-wide">MANAGED BY 1404</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            We handle setup, monitoring, tuning, and ongoing optimization. When something changes in your business, we update the agents. You don't manage any of this yourself.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-6 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-3 tracking-wide">24/7 OPERATION</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            The agents run continuously — morning briefs at 6 AM, overnight analysis, weekend monitoring. Work happens when it needs to happen, not when someone remembers to do it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-6 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-3 tracking-wide">PERSISTENT MEMORY</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Every interaction, every correction, every preference gets stored. The agents remember what you told them three months ago. Over time, they accumulate enough context that their output needs less and less editing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-border-light rounded-sm p-6 bg-bg-card">
          <p class="font-mono text-xs text-copper mb-3 tracking-wide">DEDICATED INFRASTRUCTURE</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Your agents run on isolated infrastructure. Your data never touches another client's systems. Full audit logging, encrypted credentials, and SOC 2 compliance in progress.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <CTABanner />
</PageLayout>
